ns, agencies, aesthetics and cultural production sites facilitate diverse forms of cultural activism as they challenge the dominant ways of interpreting social changes and encourage civic participation in the production of alternative meanings in and of the city. Their significance lies in their potential to question current values and power structures as well as to foster new subjectivities for disparate individuals and social groups.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aAsian Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aChinese urbanization, visual arts, representation, transition, place-making, intervention.1 aBerry, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJiehong, Jiang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandsberger, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLin, Nancy P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarinelli, Maurizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParke, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPernin, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValjakka, Minna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValjakka, Minna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWang, Meiqin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWang, Meiqin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZhang, Zhen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2